Have EC2 instances 
containerize the applicaiton 
deploy at uvic servers

Filename: redis.service
[Unit]
Description=RedisServer
After=docker.service
Requires=docker.service

[Service]
TimeoutStartSec=0
Restart=always
ExecStartPre=-/usr/bin/docker exec %n stop
ExecStartPre=-/usr/bin/docker rm %n
ExecStartPre=/usr/bin/docker pull redis:5
ExecStart=/usr/bin/docker run --rm --name %n -p 6379:6379 -d redis:5

[Install]
WantedBy=default.target


To start a service
service redis enable

service redis start

For persistance in data change the start command to match volume to container
ExecStart=/usr/bin/docker run --rm --name %n -p 6379:6379 -v /path/on/host:/data -d redis:5 redis-server --appendonly yes


For config to redis, mount redis volume


